## Conventions

| Convention | Rule |
|---|---|
| Branch name | `<type>/<issue-number>-<kebab-description>` (type ‚àà `feature/` `fix/` `chore/` `refactor/`) |
| Branch creation | `gh issue develop <N> --name <branch> --checkout --base main` (canonical issue-to-branch hop; auto-closes issue when PR merges) |
| Spec discipline | Specs ship in the same PR as code. See `docs/methodology.md` ¬ßB. |
| Living docs | Update on every ship. See `docs/methodology.md` ¬ßG + `<consumer>/CLAUDE.md` ¬ß"Documentation Requirements". |

## Context thresholds

| % | Action | Why |
|---|---|---|
| 0‚Äì50% | Work freely. | Cache warm; no concern. |
| 50‚Äì70% | Pay attention; finish current focused work before adding scope. | The next big jump degrades quality. |
| 70‚Äì90% | `/compact` to summarize. | Brings context back into a usable window without losing the thread. |
| 90%+ | `/clear` (mandatory). | Past 90%, the agent starts hallucinating from truncated context. |

Rationale: anchored on the prompt-cache 5-minute TTL + observed agent behavior under context pressure (see `docs/methodology.md` ¬ßH).

